    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="327"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d327">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/15344</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of War</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-08">April 8,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have noted your concurrence in
                    the dispatch of General Stilwell’s proposed message to Chiang Kai-shek,
                    subject—Proposed Observers’ Mission to Communist-controlled Areas in China, as
                    contained in your letter of April 4, 1944.</p>
                <p>This matter has been brought to the President’s attention. However, I do not
                    believe final action has been taken.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Henry</hi> L. <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
